summary: This isn't hate just curiosity, but has Jonah bailed on Andi in the past?
question: This isn't hate just curiosity, but has Jonah bailed on Andi in the past?
answer:
It depends on what you consider “bailing” tbh. I think that the example on costume day is the only one in which he was knowingly and purposefully bailing on her, but there have been several other times that he did so unknowingly, or at least made her feel as though he was bailing - even if he really wasn’t. Off the top of my head, those moments would include:

  • Jonah deciding to not partake in the protest in 111, but expecting Andi to change for him. Although he never agreed to partake in the protest, I think that the costume day fiasco was definitely a call back to that moment.
  • There was the whole thing in 207 where Jonah got upset because Andi laughed at him at the arcade, so he proceeded to give her the silent treatment or whatever.
  • In 209, we saw him nearly bail on her for the Grease sing-along but he ultimately chose to go with her and they had their awkward bus moment a la The Graduate 
  • At the Bar Mitzvah party, Andi felt as though she had been ditched pretty much the entire time, although it’s pretty clear that Jonah was unaware of how she felt and didn’t realize he had done anything wrong. 
  • Then there’s the whole situation at the end of season 2, where Jonah asks Andi on their first date even though he knew he was going to be out of town for the next 2 months. That was definitely……something. 
  • In 305, Andi definitely felt ditched at the lake - but that obviously wasn’t just Jonah, it was by all of her friends (particularly Buffy).

So yeah. I mean there have definitely been other situations where Andi felt as though she had been bailed on by Jonah. But the show is mostly told from Andi’s point of view, and from an outside perspective it’s pretty clear that Jonah usually wasn’t in the wrong with those situations so it’s kind of up for interpretation I guess.

summary: what do you think about the Juke shippers?? personally for me i don’t enjoy when people are shipping actors together..
question: what do you think about the Juke shippers?? personally for me i don’t enjoy when people are shipping actors together..
answer:
I’ve been pretty blatant about the fact that it’s inappropriate to ship real-life human beings with one another, especially if they are underage and especially if they are not in an openly consensual romantic relationship with each other. In the case of Juke specifically, it is even more inappropriate as it requires and encourages speculation surrounding Josh and Luke’s sexuality which is not an okay thing to do. 

https://disneymack.tumblr.com/post/181957893851/friendly-reminders-dont-ship-actors-with-their
